{"title_page": "Suzy Shinn", "text_new": "{{cleanup-reorganize|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Suzy Shinn\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Producer|songwriter|engineer}}\n}}\n'''Suzy Shinn''' is an American producer, songwriter, and engineer based in Los Angeles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glyphtech.com/news/artist-highlight|title=ARTIST HIGHLIGHT {{!}} Glyph|website=www.glyphtech.com|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/women-recording-studio-overdubbing-history-her-perspective|title=The State Of Women In Recording Studios|date=2019-03-25|website=GRAMMY.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref> She is known for her work with [[Panic! at the Disco]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.greensboro.com/entertainment/panic-at-the-disco-will-perform-at-greensboro-coliseum/article_850491d1-6b95-5186-824d-b9a4f88b3bcb.html|title=Panic! at the Disco will perform at Greensboro Coliseum|last=Triad|first=Alan Sculley Special to Go|website=Greensboro News and Record|language=en|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref> [[Weezer]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hypebot.com/hypebot/2019/04/women-in-the-mix-video.html|title=Women In The Mix - Roundtable Of Women Music Producers [Video]|website=hypebot|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref> [[Fall Out Boy]], [[Dua Lipa]], and [[Katy Perry]], among many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/02/27/588422558/if-you-want-to-be-somewhere-you-ve-got-to-occupy-it|title=How Women Are Changing The Face Of Engineering And Producing|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/suzy-shinn-mn0002808001/credits|title=Suzy Shinn {{!}} Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref> She co-wrote and produced [[Catch 22 (song)|\"Catch 22\"]] by Australian rapper [[Illy (rapper)|Illy]] featuring [[Anne-Marie (singer)|Anne-Marie]] which went on to win the 2018 [[APRA Music Awards of 2018|APRA]] Urban work of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://apraamcos.com.au/awards/2018-awards/apra-music-awards/full-list-of-winners/|title=Full List of Winners|last=AMCOS|first=APRA|website=apraamcos.com.au|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref> In 2019, Shinn also released a Splice sample pack featuring drum and vocal samples.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.noizefield.com/news/splice-sounds-released-splice-umrus-sound-cache-vol-2-new-stelios-suzy-shinn-baths-and-krs-packs|title=Splice Sounds released Splice umru\u2019s Sound Cache Vol 2 + New Stelios, Suzy Shinn, BATHS and KRS packs|last=Noizefield|date=2019-02-17|website=Noizefield|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://splice.com/sounds/splice/suzy-shinn-pack|title=Splice|website=Splice|language=en|access-date=2019-06-03}}</ref>\n\n== Selected Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Artist\n!Album\n!Song\n!Role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n|[[Weezer]]\n|[[Van Weezer]]\n|[[The End of the Game (Weezer song)|The End Of The Game]]\n|Producer\n|-\n|[[Weezer]]\n|[[Weezer (Teal Album)|The Teal Album]]\n|[[Africa (Weezer song)|Africa]]\n|Vocal Producer\n|-\n|[[Jukebox the Ghost|Jukebox The Ghost]]\n|[[Off to the Races (Jukebox the Ghost album)|Off To The Races]]\n|[[Everybody's Lonely]]\n|Engineer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"14\" |2018\n|[[Ghost (Swedish band)|Ghost]]\n|[[Prequelle]]\n|[[Witch Image]]\n|Composer\n|-\n|[[Panic! at the Disco|Panic! At The Disco]]\n|[[Pray for the Wicked|Pray For The Wicked]]\n|[[(Fuck A) Silver Lining]]\n|Engineer, Background Vocals\n|-\n|[[Panic! at the Disco|Panic! At The Disco]]\n|[[Pray for the Wicked|Pray For The Wicked]]\n|[[Say Amen (Saturday Night)]]\n|Composer, Additional Production, Engineer, Background Vocals\n|-\n|[[Panic! at the Disco|Panic! At The Disco]]\n|[[Pray for the Wicked|Pray For The Wicked]]\n|[[Hey Look Ma, I Made It]]\n|Engineer, Background Vocals\n|-\n|[[Panic! at the Disco|Panic! At The Disco]]\n|[[Pray for the Wicked|Pray For The Wicke